message: Undoing repeated vandalism for the 5th time.

Most of the pages on communities on wikipedia neither mentions their respective varna classification nor does those pages mention the reservation availed, henceforth to uphold wikipedia's policies i would like to remove these sections which in no way contributes to the page, but infact encourages discrimination, Henceforth i would like to humbly undo the edits of the vandal.

Removing regressive edits repeatedly being done by a vandal who is trying to enforce regressive backward idealogies even during these modern times, and especially mentioning irrelevant information under irrelevant categories.
This is a different Sudarshan shetty, King Sudarshan Shetty is a retired bank manager and not a sculptor.

The vandal is repeatedly enforcing the most regressive brahminical authoritarian discrimination system on this page, The entire nation is fighting this regressive supremacist idealogy, Henceforth we would like to humbly reject this Brahminical supremacist idealogy and dissociate ourselves from it, Kindly stop vandalising this page.

As previously mentioned Wikipedia articles don't help anyone avail reservations and neither is it apt to be shown in the description of the community, so kindly refrain from vandalising the page again and again.
The content is not shown in the link, so sorry can't let this poor unsourced content to exist on the page.
Removed the link and the content assosciated with it since contradictory to the vandal's claim the page and the content was not found.
The vandal seems to have attached the same regressive brahminical authoritarian discriminative ideas in many categories of the page, and Henceforth I would like to politely remove it.
Removed the edit because it was unrequited with the description of the community, and as the vandal had suggested attaching links on Wikipedia doesn't help the community avail reservations at all.

Removed" varna classification"  as its just a symbol of "Regressive  Brahminic authoritarian discrimination system", The community has made a huge name for itself with its sheer hardwork for generations now, Henceforth it is not ideal to associate it with or bully it with the regressive brahminical supremacy.

The content is sourced and approved by University grants commission, a central government body, please do not remove sourced content without reaching a consensus.

The word forward caste is also used for historically privileged communities and communities that form the minority or lesser in number are also termed OBC, and moreover no community that enjoys reservation uses petitions to avail it, and i am repeatedly saying don't make me call administrators again and again.

You couldn't establish the fact that they are not general either, Im letting your OBC category exist untill intervention from the administrators, don't make me call the administrators again and again.

The petitions mentioned by the previous editor clearly states that the petitioners claim to be from Nadavaru/Nador caste and hence are eligible to avail reservation, It has no correlation to bunt community, Bunts might be called in different terms coloquially but on documents everyone is mentioned as bunts itself, and here is the proof that bunts and Nador caste are listed separately on official government documents. https://bcw.karnataka.gov.in/storage/pdf-files/caste%20list.new.pdf
Cleared the confusion of the previous editor on the talk page with proof and hence undoing the changes.

Undid revision by anonymous user, Again "In the restricted sense" itself means he's narrowing down the community and again mentions it's "Confined to Bunt community" so this is no possibility he has pin pointed it.
Undid the changes and added citations to prove Bunts don't fall under OBC category at the central level and even in state they fall under Creamy layer/3B.
Read the source completely before reverting the edits, there's no mention of the word "possibly", he uses the term "confined" to.
Changed content based on existing citations

I have added Central government's list of OBC's in karnataka from an official government website, If you find "bunts" in this list, let me know I will revert the edit myself, Bunts compete in open category in the central level.
Using the historian's exact words as mentioned in the source.
Bunts don't have any reservation at the central level.

Undoing repeated vandalism, the link itself takes you to the page, but in case if you are not sure of the page number its page no. 101 in the book and pg 137 in the digitalized version, kindly stop vandalising the page.
Please do not remove sourced content and add content without proof.
Please refer to page no. 101, This was published by an eminent historian Mysore Hatti Rama Sharma in the year 1917.
As written by a revered scholar Mysore hatti Gopal Sharma, He writes "In a restricted sense Tuluvas belonged to Bunt community who formed the ruling class of the tulu speaking region.

Now you want to deny the findings of a guy who has a Phd in history ? Even if you deny his credentials can you deny the approval of the government body which published his research ? Don't remove sourced content.

Reverting to the best version, KN Yogeeshwarappa's research was approved by University grants commission, a complete unbiased official government controlled body, there's no caste P.O.V push here, governmental approved records are being cited here, kindly do not vandalise the page.
